      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "734ce5b0f54c285f",
      "text": "The complexity inferiority must be compensated by selection strategies. That the system is forced to selection results already from its own complexity. Which order is chosen in the relation of its elements results from the complexity difference to the environment. Both aspects can be broken down analytically in this way. However, they form only two sides of one and the same circumstance, because only by selection of an order a system can be complex. (Luhmann, [[Soziale Systeme]], 47–48)"
    }
